body:
@bolkedebruin While debugging, I noticed that the pr tool does prefix the jira to the commit message as it picks the commit message from the PR description and not the commit message. Though I still agree with you that the commit message should also contain the JIRA id (will help committers if they choose to apply manually)

Also, if you don't select the squash option while using the PR tool, it not only messes the commit message (puts message as "Merge pull request #.... from ..."), it also doesn't retain the original author of the commit. I will raise a JIRA and send a PR for this.

CC @criccomini
